## Step 5.5: Create Integration Tests (**MANDATORY**)

Integration tests are **REQUIRED** for all syncable entities. They must comprehensively cover all validation scenarios, input transpilation exceptions, and successful use cases.

**📖 See the dedicated guide:** **[Syncable Entity Integration Testing](./syncable-entity-6-integration-testing.mdc)**

The testing guide provides:
- **Complete test suite structure** (failing + successful tests for create/update/delete)
- **Test utility patterns** (query factories + wrappers)
- **Comprehensive coverage requirements** (all validators, edge cases, CRUD operations)
- **Best practices** and common patterns
- **Real-world examples** from the codebase

**Minimum Requirements:**
- ✅ Failing creation tests (all validator exceptions)
- ✅ Failing update tests (business rule violations)
- ✅ Failing deletion tests (protection rules)
- ✅ Successful CRUD tests (all operations)
- ✅ Edge case tests (sanitization, formatting, long content)
- ✅ Snapshot tests for error consistency

